Vespasian’s letter must have been written after the fall of Cremona, but before the death of Vitellius : hence he writes in the tone of a eneral whose enemy is still before him, but who is mora ly certain of victory: and son-to those who look farther than the prima species—he speaks as though the prize were within his grasp.
